@node "Introduzione"
1.0 Introduction
----------------

MtA is actually the best Videotext emulation program available for
Commodore Amiga (tm). The complete emulation of Prestel, Teletel and TTY
(Ascii) support , with many options, makes this program the ideal one for
any kind of users from the chats to the professional services.

MtA allow an easy way to connect to systems that use the CEPT2 (i.e.
French MiniTel) and CEPT3 (i.e. English Prestel or Australian Viatel)
emulation.
@endnode

@node "Hardware"				     ---
1.1 Hardware and Software required
----------------------------------

MtA works on every Amiga with at least 1.0 MB of RAM  and an S.O. 1.2 or
greater. With only 512K it is possible to run the program and use it, but
you will have some limitations on the number of requesters/menu displaied.
It's possible to use alternative serial devices (i.e. multiserial devices
or internal modems).
@endnode
				     ---
@node "Installazione"
1.2 Installation
----------------

MtA has "built-in" everything that he needs(fonts,emulation,etc.) and is
not necessary to do a complex installation procedure: the only thing to do
is to copy the program (MtA) and it's icon to your work disk or in a
drawer of your HD.

Is important that the boot disk (or HD) has the SERIAL.DEVICE (supplied
in the WorkBench disk) in DEVS:.
@endnode
				     ---
@node "Descrizione"
1.3 Short description of MtA
----------------------------

The user interface of MtA has been studied to allow an easy access to
every function of the program both by the mouse or keyboard. Also if it
looks like other amiga softwares interfaces, gives a lot of advantages.
Let's see them:

- The menues are POP-UP , that means that they appear under the pointer
  when you press the right mouse button and disappears when you press it
  again.

- During the display of the user interface data arrive from the serial
  and are saved in a buffer to avoid to loose them.

- It is possible to select a menu or a submenu using the keyboard: to
  every voice of the menu it is attribuited a number from 1 to the last
  item of it. I.e. to select the submenu "DEVICE" it is possible to click
  on the "PARAMETERS" menu and then on "DEVICE" or by pressing the key
  "5"(the "PARAMETERS" menu is the fifth) and then the key "4" ("DEVICE").

Let's show now menu and its functions: @{" General              " LINK "Generale"}
				       @{" PhoneBook/Services   " LINK "Rubrica"}
				       @{" Send                 " LINK "Invia"}
				       @{" Capture              " LINK "Cattura"}
				       @{" Parameters           " LINK "Parametri"}
				       @{" HotKeys              " LINK "HotKeys"}

@endnode

@node "Generale"
General
-------

 Authors
  Displays a requester about the autors and the modality to get registered

 Preferences
  Permits to access to the panel with the definition of main options

 Configuration
  Displays the configuration submenu

 Iconify
  Iconifys the program

 Quit
  Exits from MtA

@endnode

@node "Rubrica"
PhoneBook/Services
------------------

 Access to the relative menu for the choosing of the Telephone number or
 the service to call. The services menu appears only after the connection
 (it is important that your modem supports DCD signal).
@endnode

@node "Invia"
Send
----

 Access to the send macro menu, send service login, send file(text or VDTx
 pages) and modem commands or line break.
@endnode

@node "Cattura"
Capture
-------

 Access to the capture menu. In the demo version you can't save the
 capture file (see in paragraph 1.6 for other informations about this and
 other limitations).

 The View capture works as a VCR. After you have selected a file to show
 with the FileRequester will appear at the bottom of the screen some new
 gadgets:

  - Using the first proportional gadget or the row gadgets it is possible
    to go forward and backward trought the pages of the capture

  - The third gadget (Play) displays a page
  - The fourth gadget (C) (only if Play is activated) allows the
    continuous viewing from the actual page to the last one

  - The fifth gadget is a ciclic one and allows to simulate the speed of
    reception of data from 300 to 9600 bauds or to use the max speed of
    your processor.

  - The last two gadgets allows to load a new capture file and to exit
    from the viewer

It is possible to work also by keyboard: the relative functions hotkeys
mentioned before are the cursor keys left/right , return , shift+return,
up/down, space and esc.
@endnode

@node "Parametri"
Parameters
----------

 Terminal
  Access to the emulation standard panel, function keys and color palette

 Serial
  Access to the serial port parameters selection panel

 Modem
  Access to the modem configuration panel

 Device
  Access to the device selection panel , port and quiet data reception
@endnode

@node "HotKeys"
The main functions of the program can be used both with the mouse or keys

The keyboard sequences with "*" are not present in demo version of MtA


@{b}NB:@{ub} Amiga = Right amiga key
   Kp = Numeric keypad key



		@{" General        " LINK "Gen"}
		@{" Hotkeys        " LINK "Hot"}
		@{" Emulation      " LINK "Emu"}
		@{" Flags          " LINK "Fla"}
		@{" Function keys  " LINK "Tel"}


With a registered copy of MtA you will have a complete manual with a lot
of explanations about every function , including the (many) ones not
described here.
@endnode

@node "Gen"
General:
--------
 Amiga+Help.........About
 Amiga+I............Iconify
		    When MtA is iconified:
		    ALT-Cursor keys up/down..Change the viewed line
		    ALT-Esc..................Exits from iconify
 Amiga+Q............Quit
 Amiga+Space........Choose PhoneBook/service
 Amiga+L............Send LOGIN/PW when in selected service these fields
		    are filled

*Amiga+O............(Open) opens the capture file and activate capturing
*Amiga+W............(Write) closes the capture file
 Amiga+V............(View) showes saved capture files

 Amiga+1............Serial settings panel
 Amiga+2............Modem settings panel
 Amiga+3............Device settings panel
 Amiga+4............Emulation, function keys and palette settings panel

 Amiga+K............Macro settings panel
 Amiga+N............PhoneBook settings panel
 Amiga+S............Services settings panel

 Amiga+P............Preferences
 Amiga+F............Sends file and settings

 Amiga+ESC..........Sends BREAK on line
 Amiga+TAB..........Open/Close WorkBench
@endnode

@node "Hot"
HotKeys:
--------

 from 1 to the last menu entry

 Return.............Confirms changes (OK)
 Esc................Aborts changes (CANCEL)
 Space..............Activates first text field
 TAB................Selects next option
 Shift+TAB..........Selects previous option
@endnode

@node "Emu"
Emulation:
----------

 Alt-Del............Clears screen (useful to reset the program status)
 Alt-Help...........Shows/hides Concealed text (Prestel)
 Alt-Tab............Refreshes current screen
 Alt-Shift-Tab......Refreshes current screen with DCC codes visibled (Pst)
 Alt-Cntrl-Tab......Refreshes current screen without background

 Alt-m P............Prestel emulation
 Alt-m T............Teletel emulation
 Alt-m A............Ascii emulation (TTY)
 Alt-m E............Local echo on/off
 Alt-m L............Local mode/ online

 Alt-d 12345678.....Selects palette
 Alt-d S............Scroll mode (Teletel)
 Alt-d P............Page mode (Teletel)
 Alt-d C............Force cursor on
 Alt-d R............Loads a frame in current emulation
*Alt-d W............Saves frame (in view capture too)
*Alt-d F............Activates font definited in DRCS sequence

 Alt-k 12345........Function keys (TLT/PST/TLT X25/PST X25/PAD X3)
 Alt-k UIF..........Keyboard (USA/ITA/FRA)
 Alt-k C............Ansi (CSI) cursor keys / Vdtx
 Alt-Spazio.........Function commands window/Status window
 Alt-Kp (...........Activate functions on cursor keys
 Alt-Kp )...........Activate cursor keys

*Alt-t 1............Serial speed set to 1200
*Alt-t 2............Serial speed set to 2400
*Alt-t 4............Serial speed set to 4800
*Alt-t 9............Serial speed set to 9600

 Alt-t 7............7 bit data mode (7E1)
 Alt-t 8............8 bit data mode (8N1)
 Alt-t N............Parity None
 Alt-t E............Parity Even
@endnode

@node "Fla"
Flags
-----

 D..................DRCS
 S..................Scroll mode
 A..................Capture/save Ascii Only
 R..................Reveal activated
 I..................Autodeiconify activated
*C- (>/X)...........capture (Click on near flag to change)
 C- (N/S)...........Cursor mode (function keys/normal)

 In the status line the gray chars are parameters that can be changed
 with a mouse click
@endnode

@node "Tel"
Function keys in Teletel/Prestel
--------------------------------

 Return.............Send
 Left/up keys.......Previous	   / *#
 Right/down keys....Next	   / #
 Help...............Guide	   / *?#
 Del................Correction
 Shift+Del..........Cancel	   / **
 Shift+Help.........Repeat	   / *09
 Shift+Up...........Index	   / *00
 Shift+Esc..........Line	   / *123#

 Shift+Kp 4 6 8 2...Cursor keys
 Backspace..........BS
 Del................Prestel blob
 Kp -...............Prestel #
 Enter (Kp).........Return in all emulations
@endnode
