@node "Shareware"
1.4 What does "SHAREWARE" mean?
-----------------------------

There are three category of software: Public Domain, Shareware and
commercial ones. Now we show what are the differences between these types:

 - Public Domain software (PD): it is freely distribuited from the author
   and can be freely copied (but not saled).

 - Shareware software: the author distributes a "testing" version more or
   less limited of his product.The version of the product , like a PD
   software , can be freely distribuited. Who uses the product with
   regularity should be registered, sending money that the author asks
   for, to get a completely working version of the program. In this way
   it is possible to value if the software is find pleasant before
   buying it.

 - Commercial software: it is saled with a mail order or in specialized
   shops. It is not valuable before buying it and is prohibited and
   illegal to copy it.

MtA can be considered in the second category: is a shareware program.
Who uses it and thinks that is a valid program, he is morally bind to
get registered.

The development of this program has required more than six months of hard
work by coders and betatesters.

You can value the result in this demo version. If you think that MtA is
what you need in videotext applications, get registered. The program
support (improvements, bug fixing or modify, adding of new emulations)
depend from the number of registrations that we will receive.
@endnode
				     ---
