@node "Limitazioni"
1.7 Demo Version limitations (READ THIS!)
-----------------------------------------

This is a DEMO version an can be used only to ascertain some features
of MtA.

In this version there has been REMOVED some code's parts relative at the
functions most interesting of the program. If the pirates be able to
modify the code ( illegal act and legally pursued) in ANY CASE it is
possible to make a totally working version of the program and identical,
in might, to a registered copy.

These are the MtA-Demo limitations:

 - Serial can be opened only at 1200 bauds
 - You can configure only one service
 - Program configuration can't be loaded or saved
 - The program can be used only for a time of 15 minutes, after that they
   will be freezed and the connection will be hanged up.
 - DRCS in not available
 - After 20kb of displayed data the characters starts to be damaged and
   after 30kb they disappear completely
 - The ascii code ^P (used to exit from *pac services) are not sended
 - Can't send a line Break
 - The capture function doesn't work correctly and save only characters
   from the string "please register!"
 * It is present a full-screen banner with registration requirements. It
   is activated for 16 seconds at the start/quit of the program and in
   some disabled functions and special features of the program


The limitation with a "*" before can be activated at any time if the
program receive the sequence "REG!".

Why there have been inserted that sequence with all the other
limitations?
Many persons considers that paying for software (shareware or commercial)
is not right and for this reason they accept to use programs with great
limitations. From this the choice to offer a version almost unusefull
of MtA.

WHO WANTS TO USE REGULARY MtA MUST GET REGISTERED. THE USING OF THE DEMO
VERSION FOR DIFFERENT PURPOSES THAT ARE NOT THE VALUATION (AND TO DO THIS
YOU CAN VIEW THE LOG FILES SUPPLIED WITH THE PROGRAM) IS NOT AGREED.
IGNORING THIS RULE, MORE THAN DOING AN ILLEGAL AND IMMORAL ACT, YOU WILL
ACCEPT ALL THE LIMITATIONS (LOOSING OF DATA, LINE HANGUP, ETC) INSERTED
IN THE PROGRAM.

@{b}THE FUTURE OF MtA DEPENDS FROM YOU, THINK ABOUT THAT.@{ub}

			The authors (Franco Caprio and Michele Izzo),
			beta testers and all who have dedicated time
			(and money) to the completing of that project.

